<TITLE> Australia win the toss, choose to bat in third Test </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BIRMINGHAM, England, July 30 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Australia captain Ricky Ponting won the toss and chose to bat first in the third Ashes Test against England on Thursday. Play was due to start at 1600 GMT after a severe delay caused by torrential rain. Australia, 1-0 down in the series, made one change, all-rounder Shane Watson replacing opening batsman Phillip Hughes. Ian Bell will bat at number four for England in place of the injured Kevin Pietersen. Teams: England: Andrew Strauss (captain), Alastair Cook, Ravi Bopara, Ian Bell, Paul Collingwood, Matt Prior (wk), Andrew Flintoff, Stuart Broad, Graeme Swann, James Anderson, Graham Onions. Australia: Ricky Ponting (captain), Shane Watson, Simon Katich, Michael Hussey, Michael Clarke, Marcus North, Brad Haddin (wk), Mitchell Johnson, Nathan Hauritz, Peter Siddle, Ben Hilfen
